        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Raymond/Ruth Turner, Malkavian: A Conspiracy theorist currently obsessed with Vegas and McCarran airport, specifically. They were embraced at the height of governmental paranoia in the mid nineties, after having made contact with another “true believer” in New Mexico, convinced that Roswell was too well perceived and recorded to have been anything true. No, they knew the truth. Instead, it was a smokescreen. Something to keep people busy and from looking at the true direction. After sharing their ideas, their sire decided that their keen, deductive mind and abilities to see to the heart of the truth needed to be preserved, and they were made Malkavian. After that, they took their former obsessions and just sort of… Took off with it. They have wild ideas, especially about what happened in Vegas. That Area 51 is a hoax, and that the real base is under McCarran airport. They’ve got all kinds of crazy beliefs, about half of which end up being true, in the way of their clan. Their intuition is good, but they really do have a keen, deductive mind. If they can get directed, conversationally, away from talking about their Obsessions and Delusions, they can legitimately make good detectives, and they are perfectly willing to put their sleuthing skills to the test, and for the public good. So long as after that, everyone is willing to listen to their newest Theory."
